               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-200-person1903">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  FINDLAY
               <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1903" type="surname" value="FINDLAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1903" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1903" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an <rs id="t18191201-200-viclabel1123" type="occupation">engraver</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18191201-200-victim1900 t18191201-200-viclabel1123"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18191201-200-crimeloc1124">Merlin's-place, Clerkenwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18191201-200-crimeloc1124" type="placeName" value="Merlin's-place, Clerkenwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18191201-200-crimeloc1124" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18191201-200-off1121 t18191201-200-crimeloc1124"></join>. On Monday morning, the 5th of December, I found my workshop, which is in the yard, had been broken open, and all the tools gone. They could pass through an adjoining building into my yard. Five of the tools were found on the roof of the adjoining building. Next day I found the prisoner at the office with them - part were mine, and part Mr. Duce's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-200-person1904">
                  THOMAS 
                  MARTIN
               <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1904" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1904" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1904" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. The watchman brought the prisoner to the watch-house with the tools in his hand. I searched him, and found the prosecutor's box and eye-glass, and a piece of copper in his pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-200-person1905">
                  RICHARD 
                  DALY
               <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1905" type="surname" value="DALY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1905" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-person1905" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On Monday morning, at two o'clock, the prisoner passed me with a bundle, I asked him what he had got? he said they were tools, which belonged to his master, and I might look at them. I took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was sleeping on a brick-kiln, the watchman sent me away, and as I got down I kicked against the tools. I said I found them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18191201-200-verdict1125" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18191201-200-verdict1125" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs> Aged 16.</p>
